args:
Having beaten the demon for true, the apostles
depart Alberia with the promise they will meet
the prince and his allies again someday.
Meanwhile, in North Grastaea, Harle and a
cardinal of the Church meet for a discussion.
I've told you, it's pointless to defy me!\nSo long as I am tethered to the sealing\nstone, I am undying!
Y-yeah, I'm fine... Er, or not...?\nBut doesn't matter; this is my duty\nas an apostle.

Ah ha ha! You would throw away your life
for your precious mission? How fitting for
one of your ilk—a disposable pawn
sacrificed in vain!
I would make but one correction.

You are mistaken that their sacrifice has
been in vain, for they have bought a
precious thing indeed: A chance to see
you undone for good and all.
Is this dragon an acquaintance of yours?
Sandalphon can communicate with the\nother archangels across huge distances.\nYou might call her our central dispatch.
I called in reinforcements with her ahead\nof time, just in case things went south.\nGuess the cavalry's finally arrived.
Call all the allies you like—numbers\ncannot kill that which will not die!
Bad news, folks! I think this guy's\nlookin' to end the fight here'n now!

Allow me to end your pitiful struggling.
Kneel before my demonic might as you
sink forever into shadow! Aaaah ha ha!
AAAAAH HA HA HA HA HA!
Can you not tell? The bond tying you to the\nsealing stone you were so eagerly boasting\nabout has been cut.
Your plan worked, Ramiel: I just received\nword that Basileus safely contained the\nstone's miasma.
Our foe is now exquisitely mortal.\nDo share the will of the Goddess with him.
By the will of the Goddess,\nI will see this done!
No... NO! I am invincible! Immortal!\nThis...this cannot beeeeeee!
It sure is—though by the skin of our teeth.
Might I also point out it was Basileus\nwho ultimately dealt with the stone?
I shall endeavor to try harder next time.
We can celebrate later—these ruins\nare about to come down around us!
That demon was a terrifying foe.
Yeah, that was a metric ton'a ugly right\nthere. Still, you guys said one'a yer people\ntook care of the sealin' stone dealie?
Yes. The miasma permeating the area has\nlifted, and I believe it is safe to consider\nthe matter resolved.
Which means no more people going wroth!\nOh, what a relief.
Guess that's mission accomplished for\nyou guys, then. So what's next?
Back to North Grastaea, I'm afraid.\nI'm sure the next mission is already\nwaiting for us.
It's pretty late. Surely you can spare a\nnight to come rest in the Halidom?
Tempting, but we'll have to pass.\nIf we hurry now, we might be able\nto catch up with our leader.
That guy what handled the stone?
Exactly. He's my idol—and the strongest\napostle the Church has ever known!
I would love to meet a man whom\nyou think of in such high regard.
The apostles mostly operate out of North\nGrastaea, so I fear you may have little\nopportunity for such an encounter.
But if you're ever in our neck of the woods,\nwe'll drag him out to say hi.
Ah, there you are, Cardinal Graht!\nI've been looking for you.
To hear the results of your experiment,\nof course.
It played out much as expected.

We succeeded in driving both fiends and
humans wroth, and causing the demon
to manifest. Provided a nearby vessel,
it was even controllable to an extent.
A wonderful result, then! Er, but you said\nit was ＂much as＂ expected? Shall I take\nthat to mean there was a surprising turn?
You always were the clever one.
The demon we summoned was slain before\nwe intervened; I suspect the vessel was\ntoo weak to manage a full manifestation.
My word! And just who managed to best\na creature spoken of in legends of the\nEmpyrean War?
The apostles Ramiel brought with him,\nalong with Prince {player_name}.
Well, isn't THAT quite the fateful meeting!\nStill, I take this all to mean the sealing\nstone is no longer in your possession?
That matter was handled as planned.
Speaking of which, he has arrived. ...Enter!
Ah, so YOU'RE the sly devil who brought\nthe stone back to us, mmm?
